as weird as I can handle.

141
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:52,772
I'm not asking any more questions.

142
00:07:57,434 --> 00:07:58,441
Mom, Dad,

143
00:07:58,541 --> 00:08:01,042
there's a chance we may have
to leave here today,

144
00:08:02,074 --> 00:08:04,468
and we might not be able
to make it back, so...

145
00:08:06,095 --> 00:08:07,159
I just wanted to...

146
00:08:08,399 --> 00:08:09,541
We just...

147
00:08:09,901 --> 00:08:11,403
wanted to pay our respects.

148
00:08:12,201 --> 00:08:15,079
Remember I told you about that witch,
from the IRS?

149
00:08:15,377 --> 00:08:16,425
The one that wanted

150
00:08:16,851 --> 00:08:18,995
to take everything
you've ever worked for?

151
00:08:19,182 --> 00:08:20,293
Mom, Dad...

152
00:08:21,248 --> 00:08:22,546
this is Mimi.

153
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,322
Hello.

154
00:08:31,276 --> 00:08:32,934
It's nice to finally meet you.

155
00:08:36,082 --> 00:08:37,615
I really love your son.

156
00:08:38,898 --> 00:08:41,025
And, of course,
Bonnie is...

157
00:08:41,182 --> 00:08:42,574
she's just wonderful.

158
00:08:43,317 --> 00:08:46,311
And I've really enjoyed
living with them and...

159
00:08:46,452 --> 00:08:48,548
- Oh, great.
- What?

160
00:08:49,182 --> 00:08:51,278
I didn't say we were living together.

161
00:08:52,686 --> 00:08:53,875
We're not married.

162
00:08:56,742 --> 00:09:00,153
I'm so sorry.
I certainly... I...

163
00:09:03,141 --> 00:09:05,003
Is everything a joke to you?

164
00:09:08,545 --> 00:09:11,439
I figure one day we're going
to be buried here ourselves,

165
00:09:11,814 --> 00:09:12,816
and I...

166
00:09:13,864 --> 00:09:15,256
think it would be nice if...

167
00:09:15,851 --> 00:09:18,296
our kids came and,
and joked around with us.

168
00:09:21,957 --> 00:09:24,288
I hope that's not
for a really long time.

169
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:43,950
How we doing?

170
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:46,934
We've got about 200 men.
That includes Dale's crew.

171
00:09:47,457 --> 00:09:48,865
We got more coming, right?

172
00:09:48,975 --> 00:09:52,182
They're trickling in. It's taking
a lot longer than we thought.

173
00:09:53,746 --> 00:09:55,452
Saying good-bye to their families.

174
00:09:56,622 --> 00:09:58,632
Get on down to the pass.
Get everybody organized.

175
00:09:58,732 --> 00:10:01,381
We don't have a whole lot of time
before their advance unit hits.

176
00:10:01,624 --> 00:10:03,454
- Not you.
- Why not?

177
00:10:04,358 --> 00:10:06,263
Because these people
elected you their leader.

178
00:10:06,363 --> 00:10:08,175
We protect you at all costs.

179
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,984
And, besides, in a few minutes,
I'm going to need your help.

180
00:10:11,109 --> 00:10:12,112
Help with what?

181
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:14,777
Arming our tank.

182
00:10:22,944 --> 00:10:26,057
Our daughter is out there carrying
a rifle and... I'm in here.

183
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,747
Sam needs you here.

184
00:10:29,483 --> 00:10:30,766
You know, Allie's safe.

185
00:10:31,529 --> 00:10:32,872
She's been assigned to Town Hall,

186
00:10:32,972 --> 00:10:35,002
and the fighting is miles from there.

187
00:10:35,401 --> 00:10:38,499
Right now, there really isn't
anything else you can be doing.

188
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:44,171
Here we go.

189
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:52,257
<i>Jake, you are about
to have company.

190
00:10:52,357 --> 00:10:53,386
Already?

191
00:10:53,716 --> 00:10:55,765
<i>New Bern is on its way.
There are...

192
00:10:56,031 --> 00:10:57,940
<i>70, maybe... 80 men.

193
00:10:58,253 --> 00:10:59,778
Is that tank there yet?

194
00:11:00,028 --> 00:11:03,020
They're trying to load it
with that mortar round right now.

195
00:11:04,616 --> 00:11:06,228
I think you're gonna need it.

196
00:11:07,894 --> 00:11:10,334
All right, let's get ready!
They're coming!

197
00:11:10,632 --> 00:11:12,228
Get some ammo down here!

198
00:11:16,968 --> 00:11:17,969
What is it?

199
00:11:24,603 --> 00:11:25,807
I'm being tracked.

200
00:11:26,938 --> 00:11:28,424
Tracked?
What do you mean?

201
00:11:28,659 --> 00:11:31,710
Someone is trying to trace my location
through the satellite.

202
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:34,432
- Well, can they?
- If they have time, yes.

203
00:11:36,161 --> 00:11:37,381
Do you know who it is?

204
00:11:38,492 --> 00:11:40,448
My guess is, it's... Valente.

205
00:11:44,392 --> 00:11:47,049
What him?
From... Homeland Security?

206
00:11:47,149 --> 00:11:49,020
I don't know who he's working for now,

207
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,242
but he told Sarah
to get the bomb any way she could

208
00:11:51,342 --> 00:11:53,013
and to eliminate all witnesses.

209
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,069
All the witnesses.

210
00:11:57,663 --> 00:11:59,400
- Shut it down.
- No, I can't.

211
00:11:59,603 --> 00:12:03,554
We just have to make sure we disconnect
the feed before he finishes the trace.

212
00:13:53,602 --> 00:13:54,604
I don't get it.

213
00:13:54,893 --> 00:13:57,490
- Why are they just standing there?
- I don't know.

214
00:13:58,570 --> 00:13:59,978
Do we fire the first shot?

215
00:14:09,758 --> 00:14:10,837
New Bern's here.

216
00:14:11,901 --> 00:14:13,403
Get into position.

217
00:14:42,527 --> 00:14:44,326
We're gonna need that tank.

218
00:15:06,136 --> 00:15:07,193
Having a good time?

219
00:15:09,198 --> 00:15:11,722
By the way, I think I saw April
making out with Shep Cale.

220
00:15:11,822 --> 00:15:12,972
All right, all right.

221
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,764
You need to stop drinking.

222
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,160
Listen.

223
00:15:19,707 --> 00:15:21,691
Read this.
It's a speech.

224
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:24,461
Figure you should have something ready,
so you don't embarrass yourself.

225
00:15:24,577 --> 00:15:27,581
You mean so I don't embarrass you,
because you don't have to worry.

226
00:15:28,287 --> 00:15:30,337
Is that how you spell
"venereal disease"?

227
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:32,401
This day is important to me, okay?

228
00:15:32,864 --> 00:15:34,306
Just because your life's a big joke

229
00:15:34,421 --> 00:15:36,452
doesn't mean you have
to treat mine that way.

230
00:15:36,664 --> 00:15:38,127
Why is my life a joke?

231
00:15:38,227 --> 00:15:40,116
- Just read the speech.
- No, seriously, Eric,

232
00:15:40,216 --> 00:15:43,236
why is my life a joke?
- I'm not getting into this right now.

233
00:15:45,146 --> 00:15:46,150
All right.

234
00:15:48,657 --> 00:15:51,361
You think people don't wonder
what you've been doing?

235
00:15:51,496 --> 00:15:54,024
You spend all that time
in flight school getting your license.

236
00:15:54,178 --> 00:15:55,837
Instead of using it,
you come back here,

237
00:15:55,953 --> 00:15:58,114
hanging out like it's the summer
after high school.

238
00:15:58,335 --> 00:16:00,746
Hauling stuff for Emily's dad.

239
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,968
If I'm such a joke,
then why'd you want me as your best man?

240
00:16:12,177 --> 00:16:13,691
You didn't want me, did you?

241
00:16:14,036 --> 00:16:15,888
No, not really.

242
00:16:31,627 --> 00:16:33,087
Where's that tank?

243
00:16:33,187 --> 00:16:35,232
We're not going to last long
against those trucks.

244
00:16:35,332 --> 00:16:36,641
We have to hold out.

245
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:43,463
Damn it!

246
00:16:49,344 --> 00:16:52,149
- Got to keep drawing their fire,
all right?  - Got It.

247
00:16:56,511 --> 00:16:57,842
Give me another mag.

248
00:16:59,983 --> 00:17:01,032
Where are you going?

249
00:17:01,132 --> 00:17:03,637
We'll never get a clean shot from here.
I need to get up that hill...

250
00:17:03,737 --> 00:17:04,888
and shot on the gunner.

251
00:17:05,602 --> 00:17:07,125
- I got your back.
- All right.

252
00:17:07,225 --> 00:17:08,782
Cover him!

253
00:17:34,265 --> 00:17:36,927
Why eliminate witnesses?

